# Amanak forms — save feedback

## Explicit save (Save / Submit)

- On **successful** save, confirm with a **toast** (project uses **`sonner`**: `toast.success(...)` from `"sonner"`). Use `next-intl` for copy.
- **Do not** use inline “Saved” / green success text in the form header or toolbar as the **primary** success pattern for explicit saves.
- On **failure**, use **`toast.error`** (or `toast.warning` when appropriate) with a clear message; avoid only `console.error` for user-visible failures.

## Auto-save

- Auto-save may use a **non-toast** indicator (e.g. a short-lived **green check** icon or subtle status next to the section title) so users are not spammed.
- If auto-save fails, either a **single** non-blocking toast or a small inline error near the section is acceptable; avoid duplicate toasts on every debounced retry.

## Infrastructure

- Mount **`<AppToaster />`** once under the locale layout (`src/app/[locale]/layout.tsx`) so toasts work app-wide.
